      "<rest of content>. Write the actual literal content only."
  )

  Priority 4 — Grammar-constrained output (optional, highest reliability)

  llama-cpp-python supports GBNF grammar constraints that physically prevent the model from generating certain token sequences. J-Prime could use a grammar
  that disallows < followed by alphabetic characters, making placeholders syntactically impossible.

