  record_primary_failure() is called for all failures — network timeout, model crashed, and stale diff content. These are fundamentally different failure
  modes:

  - Infrastructure failure: J-Prime is down/unreachable → probe for availability to recover
  - Content failure: J-Prime is up but generated wrong content → availability probe will pass, J-Prime returns to PRIMARY_DEGRADED, then PRIMARY_READY, then
  fails again on the next op

  The FSM log showed exactly this: [FailbackFSM] First probe success -> PRIMARY_DEGRADED (1/3) — J-Prime passed the health probe because it is available. The
